South Africa's wing Makazole Mapimpi (L) and England's full back Elliot Daly fight for the ball during the Japan 2019 Rugby World Cup final match between England and South Africa at the International Stadium Yokohama in Yokohama on November 2, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - The Springboks are the winners of the 2019 Rugby World Cup. South Africa defeated England 32 -12 on Saturday in Tokyo, Japan. WATCH: Ramaphosa's pep talk to the Boks The Boks have now won their third RWC title. They first won it in 1995 and 2007 respectively and are now equal to their fiercest rivals, New Zealand.